WEBVTT

00:02.044 --> 00:04.879
I'm glad you guys
introduced us to Ethiopian food.

00:04.879 --> 00:06.714
And now that
I've met Ethiopian food,

00:06.714 --> 00:08.758
it's time to say
goodbye forever.

00:08.758 --> 00:13.180
It feels like it's gonna
be a long goodbye.

00:13.305 --> 00:15.682
I'm re-thinking
opening this door.

00:15.682 --> 00:17.392
Why don't you
come over for dessert?

00:17.392 --> 00:20.478
Oh, we'd love to.
Good call, honey.

00:28.236 --> 00:30.447
Coffee or--

00:30.447 --> 00:33.116
Oh, my God.

00:33.116 --> 00:34.826
Wow.

00:35.827 --> 00:37.870
You guys are pigs.

00:37.870 --> 00:41.666
I don't believe this.
We've been robbed.

00:41.666 --> 00:46.171
Wait, the window.
Adam, did you leave it open?

00:46.171 --> 00:48.047
Did you?
No.

00:48.047 --> 00:49.757
Then yeah, I did.

00:49.757 --> 00:51.926
Wait, wait. What if
they're still here?

00:51.926 --> 00:55.263
You guys stay here
and we'll go check it out.

00:55.638 --> 00:58.141
Hey, honey, I'm home from
the kung-fu studio.

00:58.141 --> 01:00.102
Yeah, and I'm home
from gun practice.

01:00.102 --> 01:04.731
Good. Now they think we're
a super-violent gay couple.

01:05.565 --> 01:08.151
Get in there.

01:10.862 --> 01:11.696
I am so freaked out.

01:11.696 --> 01:14.407
Has anything like this
ever happened to you?

01:14.407 --> 01:15.742
Uh, one time at work,

01:15.742 --> 01:18.245
someone stole a yogurt
with my name on it

01:18.245 --> 01:19.912
right out of the fridge.

01:19.912 --> 01:21.164
So no.

01:21.164 --> 01:22.999
Well, it's all clear.

01:22.999 --> 01:24.917
I checked your
underwear drawer.

01:24.917 --> 01:26.085
Your jewelry is still there.

01:26.085 --> 01:28.796
I checked it too.
He's right.

01:29.547 --> 01:31.591
So, what did they take?
I don't know,

01:31.591 --> 01:33.176
it doesn't
look like anything.

01:33.176 --> 01:35.512
Maybe when we came in
we scared them off.

01:35.512 --> 01:36.596
Hm. I don't think so.

01:36.596 --> 01:40.267
I mean, whoever did this had
time to make toaster waffles

01:40.267 --> 01:43.270
and watch 27 Dresses.

01:43.270 --> 01:46.273
Oh, that was me.

01:46.273 --> 01:48.400
I took a personal day.

01:48.400 --> 01:51.528
Well, I guess we got off
pretty lucky, huh?

01:51.528 --> 01:51.944
I guess.

01:51.944 --> 01:55.782
Or you could that say we don't
have anything worth stealing.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.534
Huh.
All of your stuff stinks.

01:57.534 --> 01:59.786
No, hold on, Jen,
they did take something.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.579
That bowl that was
on the table.

02:01.579 --> 02:03.956
The ceramic one with
the turquoise?

02:03.956 --> 02:05.917
Uh, actually
th-that's our bowl.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.669
We bought it
in New Mexico.

02:07.669 --> 02:09.086
Wait, that cost 180 bucks.

02:09.086 --> 02:11.839
Yes, I know, we brought
over spinach dip once

02:11.839 --> 02:14.050
and they never
returned it.

02:14.050 --> 02:15.218
Oh.

02:15.218 --> 02:17.094
Bad news, guys.

02:17.094 --> 02:18.680
Someone stole your bowl.

02:18.680 --> 02:20.682
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S "HOW MANY WAYS"
PLAYING]

02:20.682 --> 02:25.102
♪♪ How many ways
To say, "I love you?" ♪♪

02:25.520 --> 02:30.983
♪♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared? ♪♪

02:30.983 --> 02:33.486
♪♪ With you by my side ♪♪

02:33.486 --> 02:35.197
♪♪ There is no denyin' ♪♪

02:35.197 --> 02:39.617
♪♪ I can't wait
For me and you ♪♪

02:44.747 --> 02:47.124
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

02:47.124 --> 02:48.626
Jeff. Jeff, wake up.

02:48.626 --> 02:52.255
What? What?
Is it the burglar?

02:53.047 --> 02:54.757
Can you handle it?

02:54.757 --> 02:57.677
No, it's not that.
Listen, something just happened.

02:57.677 --> 03:00.722
Something really intense.
Really incredible.

03:00.722 --> 03:03.350
You're welcome.

03:03.350 --> 03:06.853
Awake or asleep, Daddy knows
what Mommy likes, huh?

03:06.853 --> 03:11.274
I am serious. I really
need to talk to you.

03:11.274 --> 03:12.317
Okay.

03:12.317 --> 03:15.403
Okay, now first you have
to promise not to laugh.

03:15.403 --> 03:16.738
Oh, you didn't wake me up

03:16.738 --> 03:19.574
to try on those bike shorts
again, did you?

03:19.574 --> 03:21.284
No, this is serious.

03:21.284 --> 03:23.661
All right,
I promise I won't laugh.

03:23.661 --> 03:25.247
Okay.

03:26.414 --> 03:30.001
I just saw
my grandmother's ghost.

03:30.460 --> 03:34.046
Do you mind
if I go laugh in the can?

03:35.257 --> 03:37.592
I know. I know
it sounds unbelievable.

03:37.592 --> 03:41.388
But I just saw my Grandma
Shirley at the foot of our bed.

03:41.388 --> 03:44.849
She was there, she was
wearing this garnet dress

03:44.849 --> 03:45.808
with this beautiful brooch

03:45.808 --> 03:48.561
she used to let me play with
when I was a kid.

03:48.561 --> 03:51.981
Gosh, she looked
so lovely and peaceful,

03:51.981 --> 03:54.191
with this sweet smile
on her face,

03:54.191 --> 03:56.403
like she was really happy
to see me.

03:56.403 --> 04:00.782
Probably just psyched
to be out of the urn.

04:01.283 --> 04:03.993
I'm sorry, go on.

04:03.993 --> 04:04.702
[SIGHS]

04:04.702 --> 04:06.371
I just--
I always felt so bad

04:06.371 --> 04:09.416
I didn't make it home
to see her before she died,

04:09.416 --> 04:12.001
but now I feel
like it's okay.

04:12.001 --> 04:14.504
You really saw her?

04:14.504 --> 04:15.547
I did.

04:15.547 --> 04:18.675
It wasn't like
a very real dream?

04:18.675 --> 04:21.261
Like the one I had
where me and Lee Majors

04:21.261 --> 04:23.513
were tracking Bigfoot?

04:26.391 --> 04:27.600
No.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.185
No, no, I was awake.

04:29.185 --> 04:31.729
I was sitting up.
She was right there.

04:31.729 --> 04:33.648
It was real.
Huh.

04:33.648 --> 04:35.275
Do you believe me?

04:36.108 --> 04:39.821
Yeah, I do.
I believe you.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.490
Thank you.

04:42.490 --> 04:43.783
Thank you.

04:43.783 --> 04:46.828
Yeah. I'm here for you.

04:46.828 --> 04:50.039
I feel so close
to you right now.

04:50.039 --> 04:51.833
Hm.

04:54.752 --> 04:59.424
Hey, Grandma Shirley
isn't still here, is she?

04:59.424 --> 05:02.218
I'm about
to take off my bottoms.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.346
[AUDREY LAUGHS]

05:04.346 --> 05:07.765
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

05:09.392 --> 05:10.685
Sir?

05:10.685 --> 05:13.355
I spoke to your gym,
but they maintain their stance

05:13.355 --> 05:16.065
you must participate
in the cardio hip-hop class,

05:16.065 --> 05:19.402
you cannot
just sit and watch.

05:21.153 --> 05:22.655
Call my lawyer.

05:22.655 --> 05:25.450
I contacted the accounting
firm across the street,

05:25.450 --> 05:27.118
but sadly no one
could put me in touch

05:27.118 --> 05:30.705
with "the stacked lady
in the pink thing."

05:30.705 --> 05:31.956
What?!

05:31.956 --> 05:34.709
She's right there.

05:34.709 --> 05:38.421
Pointing at me
and closing the blinds.

05:38.421 --> 05:41.508
And, sir, finally here are
all the bathing suit images

05:41.508 --> 05:43.926
of the French actress
Audrey Tautou.

05:43.926 --> 05:45.762
Yeah. Whoo!

05:45.762 --> 05:47.013
Oh, yeah. Oh.

05:47.013 --> 05:49.015
See, this is one classy girl.

05:49.015 --> 05:53.019
Ooh. Bonjour, side boob.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.563
Mercicup. Heh-heh.

05:55.563 --> 05:56.814
Good job, Timmy.
I tell you what,

05:56.814 --> 06:00.860
take an extra fiver before
you grab me my juice box.

06:00.860 --> 06:02.570
Enormously
kind of you, sir.

06:02.570 --> 06:05.281
But, uh, in lieu
of your generosity today,

06:05.281 --> 06:07.659
may I instead
leave early tomorrow?

06:07.659 --> 06:08.535
Early? Why?

06:08.535 --> 06:10.286
I'd rather not say.

06:10.286 --> 06:12.747
Say.

06:12.747 --> 06:14.123
No, thank you.

06:14.123 --> 06:15.792
No say, no early.

06:15.792 --> 06:18.085
No early, no say.

06:18.085 --> 06:20.630
Sir, I really--
Say!

06:21.881 --> 06:25.843
If you must know, I'm meeting
my fiancée at the airport.

06:25.843 --> 06:27.470
Fiancée? Ha-ha.

06:27.470 --> 06:29.305
Well, that's gotta be wrong.

06:29.305 --> 06:30.139
Uh, Timmy,

06:30.139 --> 06:34.226
are you having trouble
with your English words again?

06:34.226 --> 06:35.853
No,

06:35.853 --> 06:39.398
English is my first language.

06:39.398 --> 06:42.068
Of seven.

06:42.068 --> 06:45.697
I mean "fiancée" as in the woman
I am to marry.

06:45.697 --> 06:46.864
You're engaged?

06:46.864 --> 06:48.700
How am I just hearing
about this?

06:48.700 --> 06:51.243
Surprisingly, I have some
personal information

06:51.243 --> 06:53.455
that you've not yet bribed,
threatened

06:53.455 --> 06:55.998
or twisted my nipple
to obtain.

06:56.874 --> 06:58.167
All right,
get back here

06:58.167 --> 07:01.295
and take your shirt off.
Here we go.

07:01.295 --> 07:02.464
It's an arranged marriage.

07:02.464 --> 07:05.257
My parents are quite
traditionally Indian.

07:05.257 --> 07:06.468
It's part of my culture.

07:06.468 --> 07:09.679
Not sure
how I feel about this.

07:09.679 --> 07:12.890
How big are the old fun bags?

07:14.726 --> 07:19.439
I am not as yet familiar
with the old fun bags.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.483
She's coming to visit relatives

07:21.483 --> 07:23.985
and I will meet her
for the first time tomorrow.

07:23.985 --> 07:26.070
Come on,
you haven't even met her yet?

07:26.070 --> 07:27.447
My parents met
on their wedding day

07:27.447 --> 07:31.117
and have been happily married
for nearly three decades.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.494
Ay, caramba.

07:32.494 --> 07:35.037
Wow, your culture
sure has its quirks.

07:35.037 --> 07:38.207
It's bad enough they make you
wear the feathery hats

07:38.207 --> 07:40.668
and talk to
the eagles and stuff.

07:40.668 --> 07:44.213
It is, in fact,
not that bad, sir,

07:44.213 --> 07:48.968
because, once again,
I'm not that kind of Indian!

07:50.344 --> 07:55.016
All right, you don't have
to scalp me over this.

07:55.683 --> 07:57.727
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

07:57.727 --> 08:00.688
I just can't believe someone
in this day and age

08:00.688 --> 08:03.024
would go through
with an arranged marriage.

08:03.024 --> 08:07.028
My marriage to Audrey
was arranged.

08:07.028 --> 08:08.655
By vodka.

08:08.655 --> 08:11.616
I gotta find a way to show Timmy
he's making a huge mistake.

08:11.616 --> 08:15.119
I hate to see him forced to do
something he doesn't wanna do.

08:15.119 --> 08:17.288
You do that to him
all the time.

08:17.288 --> 08:21.626
I know. The other day
I made him touch a dead pigeon.

08:21.626 --> 08:23.711
I'm just saying,
this is New York.

08:23.711 --> 08:25.421
You can't leave the window open.

08:25.421 --> 08:26.213
I burnt my toaster waffles

08:26.213 --> 08:29.341
and I couldn't watch
27 Dresses with all that smoke.

08:29.341 --> 08:32.344
I can't believe we have nothing
worth stealing.

08:32.344 --> 08:34.972
It's embarrassing.
It's not embarrassing.

08:34.972 --> 08:36.849
Yeah, it's a little
embarrassing.

08:36.849 --> 08:39.519
Why don't you just
get some decent stuff?

08:39.519 --> 08:40.269
Here's an idea.

08:40.269 --> 08:43.355
Why don't you go
50 miles north of Santa Fe,

08:43.355 --> 08:49.612
lay 180 bucks on an old Navajo
broad and get a bowl.

08:50.947 --> 08:51.781
Hello.

08:51.781 --> 08:53.533
Wow, you look great.
You're glowing.

08:53.533 --> 08:57.036
Something really incredible
happened last night.

08:57.036 --> 08:59.038
Guilty.

08:59.038 --> 09:00.790
No, not that.

09:00.790 --> 09:03.167
Okay, you guys,
this was truly unbelievable.

09:03.167 --> 09:05.795
It was, like, 4 in the morning
and all of a sudden--

09:05.795 --> 09:08.339
Audrey, I thought that was
a private thing.

09:08.339 --> 09:12.719
No, I want to share it with
our friends. And Russell.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.679
Anyway, so I woke up

09:14.679 --> 09:16.848
and I looked
at the end of my bed,

09:16.848 --> 09:21.686
and I saw my grandma's ghost.

09:23.771 --> 09:26.065
Hm.

09:26.065 --> 09:27.149
Wow.

09:27.149 --> 09:32.113
Jeff, you might wanna hide
the key to the booze closet.

09:33.948 --> 09:36.868
We shouldn't make fun of her.
I met her grandma once.

09:36.868 --> 09:40.371
If you see her again,
will you tell her I said boo?

09:40.371 --> 09:44.041
I guess I should have expected
this. But I know what I saw.

09:44.041 --> 09:45.376
Jeff believes me.

09:45.376 --> 09:48.755
The man who's skeptical
Puerto Rico is real?

09:48.755 --> 09:51.883
Yes. Tell them.

09:53.134 --> 09:58.681
I believe that
you believe you saw a ghost.

09:58.681 --> 09:59.056
What?

09:59.056 --> 10:03.352
We don't really know what
you saw last night, do we?

10:03.352 --> 10:04.896
We don't?

10:04.896 --> 10:08.482
No. We do not.

10:09.025 --> 10:13.070
Look at that.
Printed in Puerto Rico.

10:13.070 --> 10:15.948
I stand corrected.

10:15.948 --> 10:18.951
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

10:21.120 --> 10:23.998
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

10:30.129 --> 10:32.506
Hey there, pumpkin.

10:34.050 --> 10:36.177
Wow. You look stunning.

10:36.177 --> 10:39.931
You don't really know
what I saw last night? Huh?

10:39.931 --> 10:42.850
You believe
I believe I saw a ghost?

10:42.850 --> 10:47.604
I don't believe
I used that tone.

10:47.604 --> 10:50.607
Do you know how embarrassing
that was for me?

10:50.607 --> 10:53.069
My own husband
wouldn't even support me

10:53.069 --> 10:53.861
in front of our friends.

10:53.861 --> 10:56.238
In my defense, you caught me
a little off-guard

10:56.238 --> 11:00.660
when you told your kooky
ghost story out in public.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.328
Kooky ghost story?

11:02.328 --> 11:03.996
Again,
I may be saying these things,

11:03.996 --> 11:07.667
but you're putting a lot
of extra mustard on them.

11:08.167 --> 11:09.626
So you never believed me?

11:09.626 --> 11:12.671
Well, in the moment,
I guess I-- No.

11:12.671 --> 11:14.298
So you just lied to, what,

11:14.298 --> 11:16.592
make me feel better
and get some sex out of it?

11:16.592 --> 11:20.137
Right, because I thought
seeing your dead grandmother

11:20.137 --> 11:22.639
would get you all teed up.

11:22.639 --> 11:24.475
You are unbelievable.
I'm sorry,

11:24.475 --> 11:27.686
but I can't choose to believe
something because you do.

11:27.686 --> 11:29.814
If I said something
completely crazy,

11:29.814 --> 11:32.649
would you believe me,
no matter what?

11:32.649 --> 11:33.359
I would.

11:33.359 --> 11:35.194
Well, that's just stupid.

11:35.194 --> 11:37.196
No. No.
You know what's stupid?

11:37.196 --> 11:39.448
Me thinking I could share
something important

11:39.448 --> 11:43.660
with my husband and not feel
vulnerable and ridiculed.

11:43.660 --> 11:45.747
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

11:45.747 --> 11:49.291
I am so boned
if that's Grandma Shirley.

11:51.878 --> 11:53.838
Huh?
Not even close.

11:53.838 --> 11:57.008
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

12:03.014 --> 12:04.932
Hey.

12:04.932 --> 12:07.559
Hey, you like magic?

12:07.559 --> 12:10.729
Wanna see me pull
something out of my pants?

12:10.729 --> 12:14.316
Come on.
It's a scarf.

12:14.316 --> 12:16.277
It's not a scarf.

12:16.277 --> 12:18.863
Hey, there he is.
Have a seat.

12:18.863 --> 12:20.406
Yes, I'm here.
What was so important?

12:20.406 --> 12:24.493
I've been thinking about your
little arranged marriage thing.

12:24.493 --> 12:25.077
Still?
Yes.

12:25.077 --> 12:29.081
I don't think you're focusing
enough on what you're giving up.

12:29.081 --> 12:32.919
I give you exhibits A, B, C,

12:32.919 --> 12:35.379
and double D.

12:36.047 --> 12:37.924
Sir, with all due respect--

12:37.924 --> 12:39.716
And frankly,
I'm not sure any is due.

12:39.716 --> 12:42.344
--I understand that you're
against marriage,

12:42.344 --> 12:44.889
or any arrangement
God might sanction.

12:44.889 --> 12:46.223
But I'm not you.

12:46.223 --> 12:47.809
But you can be.

12:47.809 --> 12:49.977
I don't want to be.

12:49.977 --> 12:53.815
[IN SINGSONG]
I think you do.

12:53.815 --> 12:54.982
I truly do not.

12:54.982 --> 12:58.235
Sir, this has been a custom
in my culture for centuries.

12:58.235 --> 13:01.613
And I will not be the first in
my family to challenge that.

13:01.613 --> 13:03.908
[SIGHS]
WOMAN: Oh, hey, Russell.

13:03.908 --> 13:06.452
Hey. What are you guys
doing here?

13:06.452 --> 13:09.163
What do you mean?
You're paying us 400 bucks.

13:09.163 --> 13:11.123
And no checks
this time.

13:11.123 --> 13:12.791
Take it easy.

13:12.791 --> 13:15.752
Hey, Timmy, I'd like
you to meet my friends.

13:15.752 --> 13:17.713
This is Monica.
Karen.

13:17.713 --> 13:19.548
And Susan.
Jill.

13:19.548 --> 13:22.844
It's so weird
you guys are here.

13:22.844 --> 13:25.262
[WHISPERS]
I think Monica likes you.

13:25.262 --> 13:27.056
I think
she prefers Karen, sir.

13:27.056 --> 13:29.683
Oh. She likes
the other one?

13:29.683 --> 13:31.352
Jackpot!

13:31.894 --> 13:34.897
I will not let myself
be dragged down to your level.

13:34.897 --> 13:37.233
Your life is not exactly
an advertisement

13:37.233 --> 13:40.361
for happily ever after.
Good night.

13:40.361 --> 13:42.404
Oh, so that's it?

13:42.404 --> 13:42.947
[SIGHS]

13:42.947 --> 13:47.076
Looks like your friend's not
into it. Wanna call this off?

13:47.076 --> 13:50.079
No.

13:50.662 --> 13:53.916
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

13:55.834 --> 13:58.545
Adam, look.

13:58.545 --> 14:00.339
Oh, my God, you're right.

14:00.339 --> 14:03.342
My hair is nuts right now.

14:03.342 --> 14:05.427
No, this picture.

14:05.427 --> 14:07.138
You remember
the night we met,

14:07.138 --> 14:09.306
we took that walk
through Central Park,

14:09.306 --> 14:11.392
and you kissed me
on the bridge?

14:11.392 --> 14:12.809
This is that picture.

14:12.809 --> 14:13.310
Oh, yeah.

14:13.310 --> 14:16.522
And for the record,
honey, you kissed me.

14:16.522 --> 14:19.483
I got tired of waiting for you
to make a move.

14:19.483 --> 14:20.442
Tired of waiting?

14:20.442 --> 14:23.320
I met you like
20 minutes before.

14:24.280 --> 14:28.159
Hey, let's come back
tomorrow and buy it.

14:28.159 --> 14:28.700
Really?
Yeah.

14:28.700 --> 14:31.037
We need to start accumulating
some grown-up stuff.

14:31.037 --> 14:35.374
You know, like that stupid bowl
Jeff and Audrey used to have.

14:35.374 --> 14:37.459
Yeah, we're adults.

14:37.459 --> 14:40.587
We should start
acting like it.

14:44.383 --> 14:47.053
Starting now.

14:47.678 --> 14:49.180
Starting now.

14:49.180 --> 14:52.516
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

14:53.684 --> 14:55.895
Audrey, Audrey.
What? What is it?

14:55.895 --> 14:58.105
I just saw her.
I saw Grandma Shirley.

14:58.105 --> 14:58.898
Jeff!
I'm serious.

14:58.898 --> 15:01.275
She was right here,
just like you described it.

15:01.275 --> 15:05.737
With the dress and the brooch,
all that old lady gear.

15:06.363 --> 15:07.949
All right,
it is one thing

15:07.949 --> 15:10.867
to make me feel bad
in front of our friends.

15:10.867 --> 15:11.660
And Russell.

15:11.660 --> 15:13.745
But waking me up just
to mock me--

15:13.745 --> 15:15.998
I'm not.
I saw her, I swear.

15:15.998 --> 15:18.250
And now I know
that you saw her too.

15:18.250 --> 15:20.627
You do?
You actually saw her?

15:20.627 --> 15:21.462
Absolutely. It's real.

15:21.462 --> 15:25.882
I'm sorry that I didn't support
you, it must've felt terrible.

15:25.882 --> 15:27.301
Sorry.

15:27.301 --> 15:29.595
Okay.
I accept your apology.

15:29.595 --> 15:30.054
Thank you.

15:30.054 --> 15:32.723
And you're not just
doing this to get sex?

15:32.723 --> 15:34.808
Absolutely not.

15:39.063 --> 15:41.523
[SIGHS]

15:43.650 --> 15:49.156
We could still have sex
just because, right?

15:49.156 --> 15:50.616
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

15:50.616 --> 15:51.283
This is so exciting.

15:51.283 --> 15:55.204
I know. I can't wait
to get home and hang it up.

15:57.706 --> 15:59.333
Oh, wait. Allow me.

15:59.333 --> 16:01.168
Oh.

16:02.003 --> 16:05.006
Thank you.

16:15.682 --> 16:18.519
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

16:18.519 --> 16:21.397
And then Adam turned around,
and it was gone.

16:21.397 --> 16:22.439
Well, look on the bright side.

16:22.439 --> 16:25.151
That's what I've been
trying to tell her.

16:25.151 --> 16:27.361
What is the bright side?

16:27.361 --> 16:32.158
For a brief moment, you owned
something worth stealing.

16:32.949 --> 16:36.453
Oh, lookie here.
Does the fun ever start?

16:36.953 --> 16:40.166
Well, isn't this nice
that everyone's here.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.375
Jeff has something important

16:41.375 --> 16:43.419
he would like to tell you
about last night.

16:43.419 --> 16:46.213
Isn't that right, Jeff?
What are you doing?

16:46.213 --> 16:46.922
If it really happened,

16:46.922 --> 16:49.091
you should have no problem
telling them.

16:49.091 --> 16:50.176
What are you guys
talking about?

16:50.176 --> 16:54.055
You didn't think your act last
night got you off the hook?

16:54.055 --> 16:54.680
Okay, I get it.

16:54.680 --> 16:58.892
Well, last night I saw
Audrey's grandma's ghost.

16:58.892 --> 17:02.146
And it was scary

17:02.146 --> 17:05.107
and a little bit magical.

17:05.107 --> 17:10.029
I know it's hard to believe,
but I know what I saw.

17:10.029 --> 17:11.780
Oh, my God.

17:11.780 --> 17:15.492
Yeah. Boy, did that just
give me goose bumps.

17:15.492 --> 17:19.288
Wait, you believe him?

17:19.288 --> 17:20.122
Um, Audrey,

17:20.122 --> 17:23.750
I don't think
Jeff would lie about this.

17:23.750 --> 17:24.793
Neither would I.

17:24.793 --> 17:26.253
That is a freaky story,
Jeff.

17:26.253 --> 17:29.465
I'm never gonna come to
your place again.

17:29.465 --> 17:32.468
Deal.

17:33.594 --> 17:37.139
Hold on. I saw the same ghost,
and you all made fun of me.

17:37.139 --> 17:40.767
Audrey, don't sponge off
Jeff's ghost.

17:41.352 --> 17:44.271
It wasn't Jeff's ghost,
it was my ghost.

17:44.271 --> 17:45.689
He didn't even believe me.

17:45.689 --> 17:48.317
If your own husband
doesn't believe you,

17:48.317 --> 17:50.444
how do you expect us to?

17:50.444 --> 17:54.406
No, he is lying.
He didn't see anything. I did.

17:54.406 --> 17:56.492
Sour grapes.

17:56.492 --> 17:59.411
You know, newsflash, people:
ghosts are real.

17:59.411 --> 18:01.705
Deal with it.
My friend saw--

18:01.705 --> 18:04.916
What the hell is happening here?
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

18:04.916 --> 18:05.667
This is terrible.

18:05.667 --> 18:09.755
What, are they taking
Trojan Juniors off the market?

18:09.755 --> 18:11.382
RUSSELL:
Nah, it's Timmy.

18:11.382 --> 18:13.134
He's on his way
to the airport.

18:13.134 --> 18:15.719
He's about to make the worst
mistake of his life.

18:15.719 --> 18:17.888
Wait a minute.
This has been bugging me.

18:17.888 --> 18:20.307
He's okay with
an arranged marriage,

18:20.307 --> 18:21.767
so why do you care so much?

18:21.767 --> 18:25.229
It's complicated.
Okay.

18:26.855 --> 18:29.275
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:29.275 --> 18:32.027
RUSSELL:
Timmy.

18:32.027 --> 18:32.694
Timmy.

18:32.694 --> 18:33.570
Sir,
what are you doing here?

18:33.570 --> 18:36.698
Listen, you're making a big
mistake. Come with me, buddy.

18:36.698 --> 18:38.992
I'm very well aware
of your feelings.

18:38.992 --> 18:42.454
But now I'd like to meet
my future bride alone.

18:42.454 --> 18:43.289
Okay, look, Timmy, um,

18:43.289 --> 18:47.168
I haven't been totally upfront
about why I'm against this.

18:47.168 --> 18:51.630
Uh, I know I'm not exactly
known as Mr. Romantic.

18:51.630 --> 18:54.591
Oh, I would disagree, sir.
Most women swoon when they see

18:54.591 --> 18:58.179
the "No Fat Chicks" placard
on your office door.

18:58.179 --> 19:00.013
Okay, okay.

19:00.013 --> 19:01.640
All right,
here's the thing.

19:01.640 --> 19:02.974
I actually do
believe in love.

19:02.974 --> 19:05.852
I believe there's
a special person out there

19:05.852 --> 19:06.978
for each and every one of us.

19:06.978 --> 19:09.273
That person
isn't chosen by your family.

19:09.273 --> 19:12.443
It's chosen right here,
inside.

19:12.443 --> 19:15.612
Just kiss him already.

19:15.612 --> 19:18.615
Get out of here, you bat.

19:19.866 --> 19:22.536
Sir, this is
your weakest ploy yet.

19:22.536 --> 19:23.495
It's not a ploy.

19:23.495 --> 19:25.997
Why do you think
I go through so many women?

19:25.997 --> 19:28.375
Maybe it's because
my Uncle Glen hugged me

19:28.375 --> 19:30.794
in the pool too much
when I was a kid.

19:30.794 --> 19:32.087
I think it's because

19:32.087 --> 19:33.964
I'm searching for
that special person.

19:33.964 --> 19:37.634
And that's kind of
what you're giving up.

19:37.634 --> 19:39.761
You're being sincere.

19:39.761 --> 19:40.596
Yes, I am.

19:40.596 --> 19:43.849
You deserve to find
your own special person.

19:43.849 --> 19:44.766
I--

19:44.766 --> 19:47.102
Well, I've never seen
this side of you before,

19:47.102 --> 19:51.815
Mr. Dunbar, and to be honest,
for the first time

19:51.815 --> 19:55.151
I think you may actually
have a point.

19:55.151 --> 19:55.861
I do.

19:55.861 --> 19:58.154
Don't you want
what everyone wants?

19:58.154 --> 19:59.198
That moment you see her,

19:59.198 --> 20:02.743
and you realize
your search is over?

20:02.743 --> 20:04.370
Timmy?

20:09.750 --> 20:13.003
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:17.966 --> 20:19.801
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

20:22.304 --> 20:24.055
[SIGHS]

20:26.392 --> 20:27.893
Huh?

20:27.893 --> 20:29.436
That's tacky.

20:29.436 --> 20:31.187
That's an insult to bowls.

20:31.187 --> 20:33.524
That's more of a plate,
dude.

20:33.524 --> 20:35.567
No!

20:37.736 --> 20:38.153
[SIGHS]

20:38.153 --> 20:41.532
When are we gonna tell him
we found the bowl at our place?

20:41.532 --> 20:44.743
Ah, when it stops being fun.

20:44.743 --> 20:47.454
Heh-heh. It is fun.

20:47.454 --> 20:50.916
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:53.043 --> 20:56.505
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
